            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">Available via community plugin</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 align-top bg-emerald-50">
            <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">AlertManager</th>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Built-in AlertManager datasource for viewing alerts, managing silences, and configuring receivers</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">Supports AlertManager through native alerting integration</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-slate-100 align-top bg-emerald-50">
            <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">CloudWatch (AWS)</th>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Query AWS CloudWatch metrics and logs directly from Ace with IAM credentials</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">Supported via built-in CloudWatch plugin</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="align-top bg-emerald-50">
            <th scope="row" class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">Operational scope</th>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-700">Focused product centered on monitoring and incident debugging</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">Broad ecosystem with many plugins and product extensions</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-sm text-slate-500">
      Ace is a strong fit for teams that want truly open-source, self-hosted monitoring with metrics, logs,
      traces, and access control in one product. Grafana remains a mature option with a larger plugin ecosystem.
    </p>
